messages.message: It seems Clean function does nothing on a List of Objects. When I put other simple Clean functions in, it simply didn't give any output at all anymore. The List of Objects is very useful, it would make it even more powerful if one could do Clean function on individual attributes.
a cleaning prompt should still work on list of objects!
I’ll record a quick video. It is not performing as I was expecting

i think the quick clean options only work with text fields

@Sayd @Vishnu is it easy to handle non-text fields for the quick clean functions in the backend? if not, maybe we shouldn’t show quick clean options for non-text fields?
Find here a short Loom (https://www.loom.com/share/32347822bedb4b59808705352d815fde?sid=81dde4c0-1bf7-412f-adcd-2612b368c4f0) of the issue. PW: 9krq9nuc

i think that our cleaning prompts currently don’t work well for long values as in your example

let’s wait for Vishnu to weigh in on Monday as well

this is a consistent issue we see across all large tables or lists.  It would be great to have a loop through list rows or table row and be able to refine and clean at the row level rather than the set level.
